DP  - 1981 Sep-Oct
TI  - Purposes and goals of breast self-examination.
PG  - 839-42
AB  - The role of breast self-examination (BSE) as a means of detecting early breast 
      cancer is reviewed along with some relatively unknown historical facts relating 
      to the technique. The breast is a most readily accessible site for early 
      detection which accounts for the fact that more than 90% of breast cancer is 
      found by American women themselves rather than at the time of clinical 
      examination or in special cancer detection centers. The technique of BSE is 
      briefly described as well as survey results of evaluation done in Canada, England 
      and the United States. Recent clinical trials reporting on the potential value of 
      routine BSE are presented.
