TI  - Breast cancer after Hodgkin's disease in two sisters.
PG  - 200-2
AB  - Two sisters had breast cancer at four years and 11 years after diagnosis of 
      Hodgkin's disease. The affected breast tissues had received several hundred rads 
      of scatter radiation during treatment of the lymphoma. Family history revealed 
      breast cancer in a third sister and five other women in the paternal line. 
      Cytogenetic and HLA studies showed no markers of susceptibility to neoplasia. 
      Development of second primary neoplasms of the breast in the two sisters may have 
      resulted from interactions between genetic factors and carcinogenic effects of 
      radiation exposure.
